dependencies:

 * GLPK, GLPK headers (glpk-dev)
 * pyMatProg 
    - http://pymprog.sourceforge.net/
    - encasulates of glpk provides easy interface
    - http://kent.dl.sourceforge.net/project/pymprog/pymprog-0.4/pympl.4.2.tgz
    - it includes pyglpk
    - how to setup:
      mkdir /tmp/pympl/;  tar xvpf Downloads/pympl.4.2.tgz -C /tmp/pympl/
      cd /tmp/pympl/
      sudo python setup.py install
      cd ~/; rm /tmp/pympl/ -rf
    - in case of problems I`ll rewrite it and use only pyglpk

examle of usage:
        import pymprog as mp
        # start model and define variables
        mp.beginModel('game')
        v = mp.var(name='game_value', bounds=(None,None)) #free
        p = mp.var(range(len(self.solutionsB)), 'probab')
        
        # minimze v
        mp.minimize(v)
        
        # subject to ..
        mp.st( sum(p[i] for i in p) == 1) # prob sums to 1
        r = [ mp.st(v >= sum(util[row,col]*p[col] 
                    for col in p)) for row in xrange(len(self.solutionsA)) 
            ]
        
        # solve
        mp.solve()

